<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:05PM PDT  by NWS Reno</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Pyramid Lake
through 245 PM PDT...
At 202 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Pyramid Lake, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could result in hazardous conditions on Pyramid
Lake. Sudden increases in winds and wave heights are
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pyramid Lake.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
